			<div class="content" id="post-content-3902687">
									

<p>Echoing <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/secretcrow" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3604422); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3604422&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1533698058" alt="SecretCrow" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3604422)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/secretcrow" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3604422); return false;">SecretCrow</a></span>'s sentiments. If we constrict ourselves to only writing for a certain genre, we lose out on a lot of great fiction for no benefit whatsoever. I'd be sad to lose <a href="/scp-1762">&quot;Here Were Dragons&quot;</a>, <a href="/scp-3556">Durbal</a>, or the <a href="/scp-999">Tickle Monster</a>, but those are neither sci-fi nor horror. I think that our community has become so much more than a grimdark sci-fi/horror wiki, and there is really no reason to try to change that.</p>

							</div>

								
					
